{
  "texts": [
    "Three different parts have been used for this: a feature connect mechanism with an attention mechanism, a deep neural network (DNN)-based feature generator for overall behavior, and a gated unit neural network (GRU)-based feature generator for temporal behavior.",
    "The student learning behavior data from the OULA dataset used including 6455 students and 18 features.",
    "Therefore, the experimental results showed that the proposed method offers better prediction performance with an accuracy of up to 92.5%.",
    "A hybrid DL model using a combination of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) was proposed by Xiong et al (2022) to predict student performance and discover the primary factor with the highest association with student performance.",
    "RNN was used to obtain the semantic connection between features, whereas CNN was used to collect the local dominant features and alleviates the curse of dimensionality."
  ]
}